body:
@Marjanmoodi can you try reducing `hyp[cls_pw]` and report updated results? This is the classification loss positive weight. Try 0.5 and 0.25. To enable these non-unity positive weights you also need to set the training architecture to defaultpw: `python3 train.py --arc defaultpw`

https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/53e3d55a1e002be343d49936e92c229e1d18fa58/train.py#L25-L28

Also your current results _are_ improved over your previous results. All metrics show increases: P, R, mAP, F1.
